TY  - JOUR
AU  - Barrot, Jean-Noël
AU  - Martin, Thorsten
AU  - Sauvagnat, Julien
AU  - Vallée, Boris
T1  - The Labor Market Effects of Loan Guarantee Programs
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae014
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 37
IS  - 8
SP  - 2315
EP  - 2354
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We investigate the labor market effects of a loan guarantee program targeting French SMEs during the financial crisis. Exploiting differences in regional treatment intensity in a border discontinuity design, we uncover a central trade-off for such interventions. While the program has a positive impact on workers’ employment and earnings trajectories that translates into positive aggregate employment effects, it dampens the worker reallocation toward more productive firms that happens following recessions, and particularly so for high-skill workers. This labor allocation effect is economically significant and translates into a reduction in aggregate productivity.
Y2  - 8/18/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae014
ER  - 



